  <member name="D3D_CBUFFER_TYPE">
    <summary>
      <para>Values that identify the intended use of constant-buffer data.</para>
      <blockquote>
        <para>[!NOTE]
For programming with Direct3D 10, this API has a type alias that begins <code>D3D10_</code> instead of <code>D3D_</code>. These Direct3D 10 type aliases are defined in <code>d3d10.h</code>, <code>d3d10misc.h</code>, and <code>d3d10shader.h</code>.</para>
      </blockquote>
    </summary>
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/direct3d11/d3d11-graphics-reference-d3d11-common-enumerations">Common Version Enumerations</seealso>
  </member>
